<TITLE> Chelsea sweep past Burnley, Spurs strike late </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Three goals in seven minutes gave Chelsea a 3-0 home win over Burnley on Saturday while Tottenham Hotspur left it late to beat Birmingham City 2-1 and keep pace at the top of the Premier League. Nicolas Anelka, Michael Ballack and Ashley Cole all scored either side of half-time for rampant Chelsea who made it four wins out of four under new manager Carlo Ancelotti. Aaron Lennon scored in stoppage time as Tottenham also maintained their 100 percent record, although they drop to second place on goal difference. Liverpool flirted with a third defeat of the season, trailing twice at Bolton Wanderers before coming back to win 3-2. Stoke City beat Sunderland 1-0, Blackburn Rovers earned their first point of the season with a 0-0 draw against West Ham United and Wolverhampton Wanderers and Hull City ended 1-1. Champions Manchester United and Arsenal meet later at Old Trafford in an early evening kick
